"```sql\nSELECT l.format, c.name\nFROM legalities l\nJOIN cards c ON l.uuid = c.uuid\nWHERE l.status = 'banned'\nGROUP BY l.format, c.name\nHAVING COUNT(l.status) = (\n  SELECT MAX(banned_count)\n  FROM (\n    SELECT format, COUNT(status) AS banned_count\n    FROM legalities\n    WHERE status = 'banned'\n    GROUP BY format\n  ) AS banned_counts\n);\n```\nThis SQL query identifies the play format with the highest number of cards that have a banned status and lists the names of those cards. It first calculates the number of banned cards per format, finds the maximum count, and then retrieves the format and card names that match this maximum count."